          <avActivityHighlights>The wind slabs can be released easily. or in isolated cases naturally, in particular on steep shady slopes. Weak layers in the old snowpack necessitate caution and restraint. &lt;br/&gt; As a consequence of warming moist small and medium sized avalanches are to be expected.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>Dry avalanches can be released in deeper layers also. &lt;br/&gt; And in particular the sometimes large wind slabs can be released by a single winter sport participant. &lt;br/&gt; As a consequence of warming during the day, the likelihood of moist and wet avalanches being released will increase on south facing slopes below approximately 2000 m.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>Precarious weak layers exist in the old snowpack in particular on steep northwest, north and northeast facing slopes. &lt;br/&gt;</snowpackStructureComment>
          <tendencyComment>As a consequence of warming during the day the prevalence of the avalanche prone locations will increase as the day progresses.</tendencyComment>
